Explanation:

We use a 2D array to store the count of characters in s that match t[i]. We iterate through s and t from left to right. If the count becomes zero, we move to the next character in s. Otherwise, we add the current character to the result and decrease the count. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through both s and t once. The space complexity is O(n) because we use a 2D array to store the count of characters. The energy implications are low because the algorithm only performs simple operations and does not require any complex calculations or data structures.

